  heroImg="/images/repairs/lg-gas-dryer-repair-hero.webp"
  heroAlt="LG gas dryer repair technician Los Angeles"
  heroCaption="Our technician servicing an LG gas dryer — same-day service across LA County"
  cost="$280–480"
>

  <p>LG gas dryers use a burner system instead of an electric heating element — which means when they stop heating, the cause is almost always the igniter, gas valve coils, or thermal fuse. All three are parts we carry on every truck. In most cases, an LG gas dryer that stopped heating can be diagnosed and repaired on the same visit.</p>

  <h2>Common LG Gas Dryer Problems We Fix</h2>

  <div class="gas-repair-grid">

    <div class="gas-repair-card">
      <h3>Igniter failure — most common</h3>
      <p>The igniter glows red-hot to light the gas burner. When it fails — usually after 5–8 years — the dryer runs but produces no heat. You can hear the drum spinning and the gas valve clicking, but the burner never lights. Igniter replacement: <strong>$280–350</strong>. Same-day repair in most cases.</p>
      <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-igniter-replacement/" class="gas-repair-link">LG dryer igniter replacement →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="gas-repair-card">
      <h3>Gas valve coils burned out</h3>
      <p>LG gas dryers use two or three solenoid coils to open the gas valve during each heating cycle. When one or more coils fail, the valve stays closed and no gas reaches the burner. The igniter glows normally — the gas just never flows. Coil replacement: <strong>$280–340</strong>. Full valve assembly: <strong>$380–450</strong>.</p>
      <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-gas-valve-replacement/" class="gas-repair-link">LG dryer gas valve replacement →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="gas-repair-card">
      <h3>Thermal fuse blown</h3>
      <p>The thermal fuse is a one-time safety device that cuts power to the burner circuit when the dryer overheats — usually due to a blocked vent. Once blown, it must be replaced and the root cause (the vent blockage) must be addressed. Otherwise the new fuse will blow again. Thermal fuse replacement: <strong>$280–350</strong>.</p>
      <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-thermal-fuse-replacement/" class="gas-repair-link">LG dryer thermal fuse replacement →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="gas-repair-card">
      <h3>Flame sensor failure</h3>
      <p>The radiant flame sensor monitors the burner and signals the gas valve to stay open. A failed sensor causes the burner to light briefly then shut off — clothes feel warm but never fully dry after a normal cycle. This is often confused with a gas valve problem and requires proper diagnosis with a multimeter. Repair: <strong>$280–340</strong>.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <h2>How We Diagnose LG Gas Dryers</h2>
  <p>Gas dryer diagnosis requires testing each component in sequence — igniter resistance, gas valve coil resistance, thermal fuse continuity, and flame sensor operation. Our technicians carry a multimeter and test each component on-site before recommending any parts. We never replace parts by guesswork.</p>
  <p>The $65 diagnostic fee covers the full inspection and is waived when you approve the repair. We give you a written estimate before touching anything.</p>

  <h2>LG Gas Dryer Models We Service</h2>
  <p>We work on all LG gas dryer models including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>LG DLGX series — DLGX3901V, DLGX4001V, DLGX5001V, DLGX6001V</li>
    <li>LG DLG series — DLG3471V, DLG5002V, DLG7001V</li>
    <li>LG DLHC series (LG Styler compatible)</li>
    <li>LG Tromm gas dryer models</li>
    <li>All other LG gas dryer models manufactured 2008–present</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Gas Safety — What We Check on Every Visit</h2>
  <p>Every LG gas dryer repair includes a gas connection inspection and soap leak test at no additional charge. We check the flexible gas line, shut-off valve, and all connections at the dryer before we leave. If we find a leak or an unsafe connection, we will tell you immediately and will not power the dryer until it is addressed.</p>

  <h2>Service Area — LG Gas Dryer Repair</h2>
  <p>We service LG gas dryers across Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County — including Beverly Hills, Santa Monica, Pasadena, Burbank, Glendale, Torrance, Long Beach, Irvine, Newport Beach, Thousand Oaks, and surrounding cities. Same-day appointments available most days.</p>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">Why is my LG gas dryer running but not heating?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">The three most likely causes are a failed igniter, burned-out gas valve coils, or a blown thermal fuse. All three produce the same symptom — drum spins, no heat — and require a multimeter test to distinguish. We carry all three parts on every truck and can usually diagnose and repair on the same visit.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">Is it safe to use a gas dryer that stopped heating?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">Yes — a gas dryer with no heat is not a safety risk in itself. The gas valve is closed when the burner is not lit, so there is no gas flow. However, if you smell gas at any point, stop using the dryer immediately and call us. Do not attempt to repair a gas connection yourself.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">How long does LG gas dryer repair take?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">For igniter, thermal fuse, or gas valve coil replacement — typically 45–75 minutes on-site including diagnosis, repair, and testing. We carry all common LG gas dryer parts on the truck so there is usually no wait for parts.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">How much does LG gas dryer repair cost?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">Most LG gas dryer repairs run $280–480 depending on which component failed. Igniter and thermal fuse replacements are on the lower end ($280–350). Gas valve assembly replacement runs $380–450. The $65 diagnostic fee is waived when you approve the repair.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">Do you service LG gas dryers in Orange County and Ventura County?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">Yes — we cover all three counties. Same-day service is available in most cities. Call (323) 990-7550 to check availability in your area.</div>
  </div>

